		<geography>
			<locationOfOperationSupplyOrProduction location="CN">
				<descriptionOfRestrictions xml:lang="en">This study performs a life-cycle assessment for a photovoltaic (PV) system with multi-crystalline silicon (multi-Si) modules in China</descriptionOfRestrictions>
				<descriptionOfRestrictions xml:lang="zh">本研究对中国采用多晶硅组件的光伏系统进行了生命周期评估</descriptionOfRestrictions>
			</locationOfOperationSupplyOrProduction>
		</geography>
		<technology>
			<technologicalApplicability xml:lang="en">The industrial process described is the assembly of multi-crystalline silicon (multi-Si) modules for photovoltaic (PV) systems. This involves compacting PV glass with cells and a composite material using a binder, encasing the assembly in an aluminum alloy, and installing a junction box on the back. These multi-Si modules are essential for converting solar energy into electricity and are used in both residential and commercial solar panel installations.</technologicalApplicability>
			<technologicalApplicability xml:lang="zh">本工业过程描述的是为光伏系统组装多晶硅（multi-Si）模块。这涉及使用粘结剂将PV玻璃与电池和复合材料紧凑地结合在一起，用铝合金外壳封装，并在背面安装接线盒。这些多晶硅模块是将太阳能转换为电能的关键部件，用于住宅和商业太阳能板安装。</technologicalApplicability>
			<referenceToTechnologyFlowDiagrammOrPicture type="source data set" refObjectId="7506d463-2654-e8c5-5be0-f5ac10ac3546" uri="../sources/7506d463-2654-e8c5-5be0-f5ac10ac3546.xml">
				<common:shortDescription xml:lang="en">GSvEbT284otn6Uxk366cUzLpnKe.png</common:shortDescription>
			</referenceToTechnologyFlowDiagrammOrPicture>
		</technology>
	</processInformation>
